{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.15",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 15,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 15",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 15 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:1",
      "text": "And Eliphaz the Themanite, answered, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:2",
      "text": "Will a wise man answer as if he were speaking in the wind, and fill his stomach with burning heat?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:3",
      "text": "Thou reprovest him by words, who is not equal to thee, and thou speakest that which is not good for thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:4",
      "text": "As much as is in thee, thou hast made void fear, and hast taken away prayers from before God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:5",
      "text": "For thy iniquity hath taught thy mouth, and thou imitatest the tongue of blasphemers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:6",
      "text": "Thy own mouth shall condemn thee, and not I: and thy own lips shall answer thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:7",
      "text": "Art thou the first man that was born, or wast thou made before the hills?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:8",
      "text": "Hast thou heard God's counsel, and shall his wisdom be inferior to thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:9",
      "text": "What knowest thou that we are ignorant of? what dost thou understand that we know not?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:10",
      "text": "There are with us also aged and ancient men, much elder than thy fathers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:11",
      "text": "Is it a great matter that God should comfort thee? but thy wicked words hinder this.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:12",
      "text": "Why doth thy heart elevate thee, and why dost thou stare with thy eyes, as if they were thinking great things?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:13",
      "text": "Why doth thy spirit swell against God, to utter such words out of thy mouth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:14",
      "text": "What is man that he should be without spot, and he that is born of a woman that he should appear just?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:15",
      "text": "Behold among his saints none is unchangeable, and the heavens are not pure in his sight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:16",
      "text": "How much more is man abominable, and unprofitable, who drinketh iniquity like water?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:17",
      "text": "I will shew thee, hear me: and I will tell thee what I have seen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:18",
      "text": "Wise men confess and hide not their fathers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:19",
      "text": "To whom alone the earth was given, and no stranger hath passed among them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:20",
      "text": "The wicked man is proud all his days, and the number of the years of his tyranny is uncertain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:21",
      "text": "The sound of dread is always in his ears: and when there is peace, he always suspecteth treason.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:22",
      "text": "He believeth not that he may return from darkness to light, looking round about for the sword on every side.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:23",
      "text": "When he moveth himself to seek bread, he knoweth that the day of darkness is ready at his hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:24",
      "text": "Tribulation shall terrify him, and distress shall surround him, as a king that is prepared for the battle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:25",
      "text": "For he hath stretched out his hand against God, and hath strengthened himself against the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:26",
      "text": "He hath run against him with his neck raised up, and is armed with a fat neck.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:27",
      "text": "Fatness hath covered his face, and the fat hangeth down on his sides.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:28",
      "text": "He hath dwelt in desolate cities, and in desert houses that are reduced into heaps.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:29",
      "text": "He shall not be enriched, neither shall his substance continue, neither shall he push his root in the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:30",
      "text": "He shall not depart out of darkness: the flame shall dry up his branches, and he shall be taken away by the breath of his own mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:31",
      "text": "He shall not believe, being vainly deceived by error, that he may be redeemed with any price.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:32",
      "text": "Before his days be full he shall perish: and his hands shall wither away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:33",
      "text": "He shall be blasted as a vine when its grapes are in the first flower, and as an olive tree that casteth its flower.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:34",
      "text": "For the congregation of the hypocrite is barren, and fire shall devour their tabernacles, who love to take bribes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.15.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:35",
      "text": "He hath conceived sorrow, and hath brought forth iniquity, and his womb prepareth deceits.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
